table.name: rate_service_profile
table.description: Valid list of values for names of service profiles.   The profile links rate services together in the RATE_SERVICE_PROFILE_D table.  This might be used if multiple delivery options are OK for an order (GC3 can decide which one is overall viable).  Example: rate_service 1 = 'Overnight' rate_service 2 = 'Two-day'  We could create a profile called 'Under two days', and then associate each of the rate services with this profile within the RATE_SERVICE_PROFILE_D table.  The profile links to the OB_ORDER_BASE table.

columns.name: RATE_SERVICE_PROFILE_GID
columns.description: GC3 Global identifier for the entity. Is created by concatenating Domain Name,'.' and XID.

columns.name: RATE_SERVICE_PROFILE_XID
columns.description: GC3 Unique identifier for the entity. Is used for creating the GID
